# EtherCAT DC Lock Check

Open this notebook with a Mix project runtime rooted at this repository.

Use the setup Smart Cell to configure a DC-enabled session first. The cells
below then verify that the master reaches the expected Distributed Clocks lock
state and show the final runtime snapshot.

## Setup

<!-- livebook:{"attrs":"e30","chunks":null,"kind":"Elixir.KinoEtherCAT.SmartCells.Setup","livebook_object":"smart_cell"} -->

```elixir

```

## Helpers

```elixir
await_dc_lock = fn expected_state, timeout_ms, poll_ms ->
  deadline = System.monotonic_time(:millisecond) + timeout_ms
  samples = []

  Stream.repeatedly(fn -> EtherCAT.dc_status() end)
  |> Enum.reduce_while(samples, fn status, acc ->
    current =
      %{
        at_ms: System.system_time(:millisecond),
        lock_state: status.lock_state,
        max_sync_diff_ns: status.max_sync_diff_ns
      }

    cond do
      status.lock_state == expected_state ->
        {:halt, {:ok, Enum.reverse([current | acc])}}

      System.monotonic_time(:millisecond) >= deadline ->
        {:halt, {:error, {:timeout, Enum.reverse([current | acc])}}}

      true ->
        Process.sleep(poll_ms)
        {:cont, [current | acc]}
    end
  end)
end
```

## Configuration

```elixir
expected_lock_state = :locked
timeout_ms = 10_000
poll_ms = 50
```

## Run

```elixir
with {:ok, samples} <- await_dc_lock.(expected_lock_state, timeout_ms, poll_ms) do
  %{
    status: :ok,
    expected_lock_state: expected_lock_state,
    final_status: EtherCAT.dc_status(),
    samples: samples
  }
else
  {:error, {:timeout, samples}} ->
    %{
      status: :error,
      expected_lock_state: expected_lock_state,
      final_status: EtherCAT.dc_status(),
      samples: samples
    }
end
```

## Tidy Up

```elixir
EtherCAT.dc_status()
